=93maximization algorithm</a> (EM): the prediction step inside the loop is =
the <i>E</i>-step of EM, while the re-training of naive Bayes is the <i>M</=
i>-step. The algorithm is formally justified by the assumption that the dat=
a are generated by a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mixture_model=
" title=3D"Mixture model">mixture model</a>, and the components of this mix=
ture model are exactly the classes of the classification problem.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-em_15-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
