<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Document_classification">Do=
cument classification</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DNaive_Bayes_classifier&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D15" title=
=3D"Edit section: Document classification"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Here is a worked example of naive Bayesian classification to the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Document_classification" title=3D"Documen=
t classification">document classification</a> problem.
Consider the problem of classifying documents by their content, for example=
 into <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spamming" title=3D"Spamming"=
>spam</a> and non-spam <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E-mail" cla=
ss=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"E-mail">e-mails</a>. Imagine that documents are=
 drawn from a number of classes of documents which can be modeled as sets o=
f words where the (independent) probability that the i-th word of a given d=
ocument occurs in a document from class <i>C</i> can be written as
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle p(w_{i}\mid C)\,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>p</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>w</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=88=A3<!-- =E2=88=A3 --></mo>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p(w_{i}\mid C=
)\,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/31d6dee54454209ba0810f0ce4f43bc087a89a9c" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:9.623ex; height:2.843ex;" a=
lt=3D"{\displaystyle p(w_{i}\mid C)\,}"></span>
</p><p>(For this treatment, things are further simplified by assuming that =
words are randomly distributed in the document - that is, words are not dep=
endent on the length of the document, position within the document with rel=
ation to other words, or other document-context.)
</p><p>Then the probability that a given document <i>D</i> contains all of =
the words <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cl=
ass=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;=
"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displayst=
yle w_{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>w</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle w_{i}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fe22f0329d3ecb2e1880d44d191aba0e5475db68" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.464ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle w_{=
i}}"></span>, given a class <i>C</i>, is
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle p(D\mid C)=3D\prod _{i}p(w_{i}\mid C)\,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>p</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>D</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=A3<!-- =E2=88=A3 --></mo>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <munder>
